1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,000
Extra CO2 doesn’t just warm the air—it changes our oceans.

2
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:08,800
As CO2 dissolves in seawater, it forms carbonic acid, altering pH levels.

3
00:00:08,800 --> 00:00:13,600
This impacts carbonate ions, essential for shell-building creatures like corals and mollusks.

4
00:00:13,600 --> 00:00:17,200
But it’s not all grim—marine life is remarkably resilient.

5
00:00:17,200 --> 00:00:22,000
Research is ongoing, and scientists are finding ways to help ecosystems adapt.

6
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:26,000
Stay curious and explore how we can protect our oceans.

7
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:28,800
Like and follow for more science insights!
